    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Increased border security and stricter immigration enforcement are not just about keeping out illegal immigrants; they are about upholding the very foundation of our society: the rule of law. When we fail to secure our borders, we create a situation where those who have entered through legal means are put in a precarious position. This undermines their legal status and the integrity of our immigration system. By allowing illegal immigration to go unchecked, we send a message that the law is not absolute, which can lead to a breakdown in societal order. Stricter enforcement ensures that everyone, regardless of their origin, is subject to the same laws, thereby maintaining fairness and justice. It also sends a clear message that our nation values the rule of law above all, which is essential for a stable and prosperous society. By prioritizing border security, we protect the legal rights of those who have followed the proper channels and uphold the integrity of our legal system.",
